properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide running water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and by a secondary application, which is tropical. (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trench"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which it runs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb, TA *:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohurN","text_ar":"اَنْهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) a pl. of the former, (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohaArN","text_ar":"اَنْهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) a pl. of the latter, (Msb,) [but used as a pl. of either, both of pauc. and of mult. and the most common of all the pls.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhurN","text_ar":"نُهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, and so in some copies of the K,) with two dammehs, a pl. of the former, (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhorN","text_ar":"نُهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in some copies of the K and in the TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhuwrN","text_ar":"نُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY","text_ar":"جَرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ahoru","text_ar":"النَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The river ran,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY AlmiyzaAbu","text_ar":"جَرَى المِيزَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN kaviyr AlmaA='i","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ كَثِير المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A channel of running water having much water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naharN","text_ar":"نَهَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in a pl. sense: as in the Kur, [liv. 54],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY jan~aAtK wanaharK","text_ar":"فِى جَنَّاتٍ وَنَهَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In gardens and"},{"kind":"text","text":"among"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivers"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohaAri","text_ar":"اَنْهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like the phrase in the Kur, (same chap. verse 45,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayuwal~uwna Ald~ubora","text_ar":"وَيُوَلُّونَ الدُّبْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, S.) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^adobaAra","text_ar":"الاَدْبَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, TA:) but it is otherwise explained. (S.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naharN","text_ar":"نَهَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","Fr"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}